---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Privacy Policy | Mellon"
  description="Mellon and Habitedge Pty Ltd privacy policy. We do not collect, store, or transmit your voice data or personal information."
>
  <section class="privacy-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="privacy-updated">Last updated: February 2025</p>

      <div class="privacy-content">
        <div class="privacy-block">
          <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            Habitedge Pty Ltd ("we", "our", or "us") operates Mellon Voice and related products. We are committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we handle information when you use our software and websites.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-block">
          <h2>2. Mellon Voice — No Data Collection</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Mellon Voice processes all speech locally on your Mac.</strong> We do not collect, store, transmit, or have access to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your voice recordings</li>
            <li>What you dictate</li>
            <li>Any text you generate using Mellon</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Speech recognition runs entirely on your device. No voice or text data is sent to our servers or any third party.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-block">
          <h2>3. Information We May Collect</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Website usage:</strong> When you visit mellonvoice.com or related sites, we may collect standard analytics (e.g., page views, referrer) through services that help us improve the site. This does not include personally identifiable information unless you provide it (e.g., via a contact form).
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>License activation:</strong> If you use a paid license, our payment processor (e.g., Gumroad) may collect payment information. We receive only what is necessary to fulfill your purchase (e.g., email for license delivery). We do not store credit card details.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-block">
          <h2>4. How We Use Information</h2>
          <p>
            Any information we receive is used only to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Deliver licenses or support you request</li>
            <li>Improve our products and website</li>
            <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-block">
          <h2>5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
          <p>
            Mellon Voice does not store your data on our servers—it stays on your Mac. For any data we do hold (e.g., support emails), we use reasonable measures to keep it secure.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-block">
          <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal data we hold. Contact us at <a href="mailto:daniel@habitedge.app">daniel@habitedge.app</a> to exercise these rights.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-block">
          <h2>7. Children</h2>
          <p>
            Our products are not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-block">
          <h2>8. Changes</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top reflects the latest version. Continued use of our products after changes constitutes acceptance.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="privacy-block">
          <h2>9. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Habitedge Pty Ltd<br />
            Email: <a href="mailto:daniel@habitedge.app">daniel@habitedge.app</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-section {
    padding: var(--space-5xl) 0;
    min-height: 60vh;
  }

  .privacy-title {
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .privacy-updated {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .privacy-content {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .privacy-block {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .privacy-block h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .privacy-block p, .privacy-block li {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .privacy-block ul {
    margin: var(--space-sm) 0 var(--space-md);
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .privacy-block a {
    color: var(--color-accent-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .privacy-block a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .privacy-block {
      padding: var(--space-xl);
    }
  }
</style>
